In [27]:
def make_3d(gray_img):
    # indexing with np.newaxis inserts a new 3rd dimension, which we then repeat the
    # array along, (you can achieve the same effect by indexing with None)
    return np.repeat(gray_img[:, :, np.newaxis], 3, axis=2)

def show_corners(corners, src_img):
    src_copy = np.copy(src_img)
    for i,j in corners:
        cv.circle(src_copy, (round(j),round(i)), 4,  (255, 0, 0), cv.FILLED)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,12))
    plt.imshow(src_copy, cmap='gray')
                
    
def pad_with(vector, pad_width, iaxis, kwargs):
    pad_value = kwargs.get('padder', 0)
    vector[:pad_width[0]] = pad_value
    vector[-pad_width[1]:] = pad_value

In [29]:
# PREDICTION
import time
possible_corners_list = corner_coords.tolist()
batch = []
coords = []
true_corners = []
batch_size = 64
start = time.time()
for i, j in possible_corners_list:
    k = round(i) + patch_width # to get out of the 0 padding
    l = round(j) + patch_width # to get out of the 0 padding
    clean_corner_image = make_3d(padded_src_gray[
        k-patch_width:k+patch_width,
        l-patch_width:l+patch_width
    ])
    coords.append((i,j))
    batch.append(clean_corner_image)
    if len(batch) == batch_size:
        x = np.stack(batch)
        preds = [round(p_.item()) for p_ in model.predict(x, batch_size)]
        for coord, p in zip(coords, preds):
            if p == 1:
                true_corners.append(coord)
        batch = []
        coords = []
if len(batch) > 0:
    x = np.stack(batch)
    preds = [round(p_.item()) for p_ in model.predict(x, len(batch))]
    for coord, p in zip(coords, preds):
        if p == 1:
            true_corners.append(coord)
print(time.time() - start)
print(len(true_corners))
show_corners(true_corners, src_small)
